625.
CHARLES FAIRBANK
, feloniously forging and uttering on 8th May, a request for the delivery of 6 watches;
also. on 8th May, another request for the delivery of 6 watches;
also, on 14th April, one other request for the delivery of 6 watches, with intent to defraud: to which he





     JOSEPH COOKE
(policeman). I produce a certificate—(read—Clerkewell; 


     John Brown, convicted, Jan., 1852, of stealing a yard measure, and other articles; confined four months)—I was present—Swann is the man, I have not a shadow of a doubt.
